        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 4:20AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 420 AM CDT/320 AM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm over Nadine, or near Hobbs, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hobbs, Nadine, Knowles, and Lea County Regional Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
